race.comment: Tricky. SWEETHEARTED (10) had been threatening to win one this time in and got the job done at Geelong last time out over 1100m. Stays in BM84 company and this doesn't look much harder, he'll be slicing his way through late. STEEL MOVE (3) is flying. He's won two of his past three, winning a rich race at Cranbourne last time out. Nearing double figures in early betting seems more than fair. DIRTY GRIN (6) was okay in a good BM84 second up at Pakenham when getting too far back. The fresh win with 61kg was good, he can bounce back. IMMORTAL STAR (12) gets in under the minimum after Bates' claim. She's racing well and should get a nice trailing run behind the speed. MOBY DICK (9) wasn't far off SWEETHEARTED fresh and his best is absolutely good enough to win this, wary.
